Problem Statement 01:
“Energy Relay Network”
A robot is traveling through a sequence of energy stations.
You are given an array energy[] where:
energy[i] represents the energy gained (positive) or lost (negative) at station i.
The robot starts at index 0 and wants to reach index n - 1.
From any station i, it may jump:
to i + 1
or to i + 2
However, the robot’s energy core overheats if it lands on more than 2 negative stations consecutively.
Return the maximum total energy the robot can collect while reaching the last station.
If reaching the end is impossible, return -1.

Example
Input
energy = [4, -5, -2, 3, -1, 6]
Output
11



